# ============================================================
# HOW IT WORKS
# ============================================================

st.divider()

with st.expander("⚙️ How It Works"):
    st.markdown(
        """
        ```
        Customer Query
              ↓
        🧭 Query Analyzer       → classifies category, urgency, sentiment, complexity
              ↓
              ├── Simple query? ──────────────┐
              │                                │
              ▼                                ▼
        🤖 Assistant (RAG-grounded)      🤖 Assistant (RAG-grounded)
              │                                ↓
              │                          🌐 Web Search Assistant + sources
              │                                ↓
              │                          🧪 Quality Synthesizer (confidence + follow-ups)
              │                                │
              └──────────────┬─────────────────┘
                              ↓
                       📝 Entry Agent → SQLite database (support_log table)
        ```

        **Retrieval-augmented generation:** the Assistant's answers are grounded
        in `solar_project_knowledge_base.txt`, chunked and indexed with TF-IDF.
        The most relevant excerpts (cosine similarity ≥ 0.08) are injected into
        its prompt before it answers.

        **Conditional routing:** the Query Analyzer decides whether a question
        is Simple or Complex. Simple questions skip the Web Search and Quality
        Synthesizer agents entirely — roughly halving LLM calls for routine
        questions. Any query flagged High/Critical urgency or Frustrated
        sentiment is always forced onto the full verification path,
        regardless of what the classifier says.

        **Structured storage:** every interaction — including its
        classification and which path it took — is saved to a SQLite table
        with a fixed schema, so the history is queryable, not just a flat
        append-only text file.

        Near-duplicate questions asked in the same session are matched and
        answered instantly from the session cache, skipping agent execution
        altogether.
        """
    )


